il. Routledge, 2009, pp. 99-102. textbook:Katznelson, Ira. "Social Justice, Liberalism and the City: Considerations on David Harvey, John Rawls and Karl Polanyi." The Urbanization of Injustice. Edited by Andy Merrifeild, and E. Swyngedouw. New York University Press, 1997, pp. 45-64. textbook:Brenner, Neil. "'Glocalization' as a State Spatial Strategy: Urban Entrepreneurialism and the New Politics of Uneven Development in Western Europe." Remaking the Global Economy: Economic-Geographical Perspectives. Edited by Jamie Peck, and Henry Yeung. Sage, 2003, pp. 197-215. textbook:Al-Shejni, Lamis A. M. "Politics of Place in Multilevel Games: Are Arab Women Acting or Reacting?" Making the Invisible Visible: A Multicultural Planning History. Edited by Leonie Sandercock. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1998. textbook:Susskind, Lawrence, and Jeffrey L. Cruikshank. Chapter 2 and appendix A in Breaking Robert's Rules: The New Way to Run Your Meeting, Build Consensus, and Get Results. Oxford University Press, 2006. textbook:Flyvbjerg, Bent. "Power Has a Rationality That Rationality Does Not Know." Rationality and Power: Democracy in Practice. University of Chicago Press, 1998, pp. 225-36. textbook:Martinotti, Guido. "A City for Whom? Transients and Public Life in the Second-Generation Metropolis." The Urban Moment: Cosmopolitan Essays on the Late-20th-Century City. Edited by A. Beauregard, and Sophie Body-Gendrot. Sage Publications, 1999, pp. 155-184. textbook:Fainstein, Susan S. The Just City. Cornell University Press, 2010. textbook:Nozick, Robert. "Utopian Means and Ends." In Anarchy, State, and Utopia. Basic Books, 1974, pp. 326-334. textbook:Marcuse, Herbert, Robert Paul Wolff, and Barrington Moore, Jr. "Repressive Tolerance." A Critique of Pure Tolerance." Beacon Press, 1997, pp. 95-137. textbook:Sen, Amartya. "Institutions and Persons." The Idea of Justice. Belknap Press of Harvard University Press, 2009, pp. 75-113. textbook:Walzer, Michael. Preface, early part 