11.491 | Economic Development and Policy Analysis | https://www.google.com.hk/?gws_rd=cr,ssl#safe=strict&q=11.491 Economic Development and Policy Analysis | prereq:11.701 instructors:Staff term:G (Fall) Not offered regularly; consult department description:Examines the process of economic development to understand why some countries or regions within countries have increased their incomes and reduced their poverty faster than others. Economic development is treated as a process of learning, as countries weigh theories and role models as guides for policy formulation and institution building. Historical and empirical examination of three role models for development/underdevelopment, as formulated by the Third World's new intelligentsia that emerged after de-colonization: the OPEC development role model, the East Asian role model, and the Brazilian role model. Same subject as 17.176[J] 3-0-9 units
